  "datePublished": "2026-04-02",
  "description": "Double fertilization: the defining reproductive innovation of angiosperms, in which a single pollen tube delivers two sperm cells to the ovule. One sperm fuses with the egg cell to form the diploid zygote that will develop into the embryo; the other fuses with the central cell\u0026rsquo;s two polar nuclei to form the triploid endosperm. This two-for-one event is unique to flowering plants and ensures that endosperm is produced only when fertilization occurs, eliminating wasted provisioning of unfertilized ovules.\n",
